# Sample environment for SAS_Parser — copy to `.env` and fill in.
#
#   cp .env.example .env      # (.env is gitignored; never commit real values)
#
# demo_run.py auto-loads `.env` from the repo root (via python-dotenv) at
# startup; real shell environment variables still win over the file. These are
# the variables app_config.vault and demo_run.py read. Non-secret Vault knobs
# (mount_point, kv_version, timeout, verify) live in the `vault` section of
# config.json, not here.

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# LLM API key — the direct (no-Vault) path
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Used when demo_run.py is run WITHOUT --vault-secret. Ignored when the key is
# fetched from Vault instead.
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Vault connection (non-secret) — standard HashiCorp env vars
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Address wins over config.json vault.address; required to reach Vault.
VAULT_ADDR=https://vault.example:8200
# Vault Enterprise namespace; leave unset for open-source / root namespace.
#VAULT_NAMESPACE=team-sas
# TLS: path to a CA bundle to trust, or set VAULT_SKIP_VERIFY=true to disable
# verification (DEV ONLY — never in production).
#VAULT_CACERT=/etc/ssl/vault-ca.pem
#VAULT_SKIP_VERIFY=false

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Vault auth — pick ONE method (secrets: keep out of source control)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# AppRole (app-based auth) — what demo_run.py --vault-secret uses. The app
# authenticates as its own identity with a role_id / secret_id pair.
VAULT_ROLE_ID=00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000
VAULT_SECRET_ID=00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000

# Token auth — an alternative to AppRole for the library's from_env() path.
# (demo_run.py deliberately ignores this and forces AppRole.) Uncomment to use.
#VAULT_TOKEN=hvs.xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# SharePoint (Microsoft Graph) — app_config.sharepoint
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# No secrets here: SharePoint auth is delegated to the Entra ID service
# principal above (AZURE_TENANT_ID / AZURE_CLIENT_ID / AZURE_CLIENT_SECRET),
# whose app registration needs the Graph application permission
# Sites.ReadWrite.All granted with admin consent. Non-secret knobs (drive_id,
# scopes, timeout) may instead live in the `sharepoint` section of config.json.
# Identify the site with SHAREPOINT_SITE_ID, or the hostname + path pair:
#SHAREPOINT_SITE_HOSTNAME=contoso.sharepoint.com
#SHAREPOINT_SITE_PATH=/sites/Engineering
#SHAREPOINT_SITE_ID=contoso.sharepoint.com,00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000,00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000
# Target a specific document library; omit to use the site's default library:
#SHAREPOINT_DRIVE_ID=b!xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Optional: point at an alternative config.json (app_config loader)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
#SAS_PARSER_CONFIG=/path/to/config.json
